56199144-d2f1-4c24-8da0-8c733075a177.77759be5-1f05-446e-813f-d74ad4930a88.prompt=Enter a value for enabled 56199144-d2f1-4c24-8da0-8c733075a177.969fbdd3-6de7-4d67-8f5a-e933d315c01c.description=
Authenticates against a keystone identity service and returns an authentication token and a list of endpoints available to the specified user. This flow should handle authentication against public/private cloud systems installed using the default procedure outlined in the OpenStack administrators guide, as well as the HP cloud services public cloud. 
There are two endpoints returned by this flow\:  and , which are HP plugin extensions to OpenStack, and these two outputs will be empty if this flow is run against a generic Keystone implementation. 

Inputs\:
    identityServiceEndpoint - The endpoint to which authentication requests are sent. 
Example\: https\://region-a.geo-1.identity.hpcloudsvc.com\:35357/v2.0
    identityServiceUsername - The keystone authentication user name.
Examples\: admin, user@somedomain.com
    identityServicePassword - The keystone authentication password.
Example\: somepassword
    tenantId - The ID of the keystone tenant used in the authentication process.
Examples\: 123456798, 86aae2e3c911436c986999b8d930c073
    computeRegion - The region from which to select the compute endpoint. This is also used for image block storage endpoints. If this input is empty, the first endpoint in the returned array of endpoints is selected. 
Example\: az-2.region-a.geo-1
    objectStorageRegion - The region of the object storage endpoint to select. This region is also used for the CDN endpoint. If the region is not specified, the first endpoint in the returned array of endpoints is selected.
Example\: region-a.geo-1
    username - The user name used for URL authentication. For NTLM authentication, the required format is 'domain\user'.
    password - The password used for URL authentication.
    authType - The type of authentication used by this operation when trying to execute the request on the target server.
Valid values\: basic, form, digest, ntlm, kerberos, anonymous (no authentication)
Default value\: anonymous (no authentication used when executing the request)
    kerberosConfFile - The path to the Kerberos configuration file. If this input is empty, the  (Key Distribution Center) and  get their values from the full domain name obtained from the web server URL.
    timeout - The time to wait for a connection to be established, in  milliseconds. This input needs a value greater than or equal to zero. A  value of '0' represents an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0
    socketTimeout - The time to wait for data to be retrieved, in milliseconds. This input needs a value greater than or equal to zero. A  value of '0' represents an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0
    useCookies - Specifies whether to enable cookie tracking or not. Cookies are stored between consecutive calls. If you specify a non-Boolean value, the default value is used. 
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: true
    proxy - The proxy server used to access the web site.
    proxyPort - The proxy server port.
    proxyUsername - The proxy server user name.
    proxyPassword - The proxy server password associated with the  input value.
    encodeURL - Specifies whether to encode the URL or not. If you specify a non-Boolean value, the default value is used. 
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: false
    characterSet - The character encoding to be used for the HTTP 'Get' request and response. 
Default value\: UTF-8
    trustAllRoots - Specifies whether to enable weak security over SSL. A SSL certificate is trusted even if no trusted certification authority issued it.
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: true
    keystore - The location of the KeyStore file - a URL or the local path to it. This input is empty if no HTTPS client authentication is used. The default value will be provided if trustAllRoots is false.
Default\: /java/lib/security/cacerts
    keystorePassword - The password associated with the KeyStore file. If trustAllRoots is false and keystore is empty, keystorePassword default will be supplied.
Default value\: changeit
    trustKeystore - The location of the TrustStore file - a URL or the local path to it. This input is empty if no HTTPS server authentication is used. The default value will be provided if trustAllRoots is false.
Default\: /java/lib/security/cacerts
    trustPassword - The password associated with the TrustStore file.  If trustAllRoots is false and trustKeystore is empty, trustPassword default will be supplied.
Default value\: changeit
    headerNamesList - A list of header names to be used for the request.
Example\: Accept,Content-Type
    headerValuesList - A list of header values to be used for the request. 
Example\: text/plain,application/x-www-form-urlencoded
    queryNamesList - A list of query parameter names to be used for the request. 
Example\: parameterName1,parameterName2 
    queryValuesList - A list of query parameter values to be used for the request. 
Example\: parameterValue1,parameterValue2
    delimiter - The delimiter used to separate list elements.
Default value\: (carriage return)

Results\:
    authToken - This is the primary output. The token needed for subsequent API calls.
    FailureMessage - The final error message returned to the user.
    objectStorageEndpoint - The endpoint to use for object storage (swift) API calls.
    cdnEndpoint - The endpoint to use for CDN API calls.
    blockStorageEndpoint- The endpoint to use for block storage API calls.
    computeEndpoint - The endpoint to use for compute (nova) API calls.
    imageEndpoint - The endpoint to use for image (glance) API calls.  
    accessJSONObject - The complete JSON object returned by the authentication request.
    exception - The stack trace of the thrown error (if an error occurred).

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.
    unknown - The authentication request resulted in an INFORMATIONAL or REDIRECTION code. This usually means that the request failed.

Note\:
See the 'Library/Operations/HTTP Client/' operations for additional information.
56199144-d2f1-4c24-8da0-8c733075a177.cd423f59-801b-420d-922c-895c8bc7031d.prompt=Enter a value for projectName 56199144-d2f1-4c24-8da0-8c733075a177.fbc11dfc-b27a-4060-9d36-dc8957835ff1.description=
Creates an OpenStack Identity project to organize users.

Inputs\:
    identityEndpoint - The endpoint to which requests are sent.
Example\: http\://16.77.62.235\:5000
    authToken - The authentication token used for the request.
Example\: HPAuth_4f3b5044e4b05c3dbefdee82
    projectName - The name given to the created project.
    projectDescription - The description of the created project.
    domainId - The domain ID of the created project.
    enabled - Sets the enabled property for the created project. By default the project is enabled.
Valid values\: true, false 
Default value\: null
    username - The user name used for URL authentication. For NTLM authentication, the required format is 'domain\user'.
    password - The password used for URL authentication.
    authType - The type of authentication used by this operation when trying to execute the request on the target server.
Valid values\: basic, form, digest, ntlm, kerberos, anonymous (no authentication)
Default value\: anonymous (no authentication used when executing the request)
    timeout - The time to wait for a connection to be established, in  milliseconds. This input needs a value greater than or equal to zero. A  value of '0' represents an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0
    socketTimeout - The time to wait for data to be retrieved, in milliseconds. This input needs a value greater than or equal to zero. A  value of '0' represents an infinite timeout. 
Default value\: 0
    useCookies - Specifies whether to enable cookie tracking or not. Cookies are stored between consecutive calls. If you specify a non-Boolean value, the default value is used. 
Valid values\: true, false 
Default value\: true
    proxy - The proxy server used to access the web site.
    proxyPort - The proxy server port.
    proxyUsername - The proxy server user name.
    proxyPassword - he proxy server password associated with the  input value.
    encodeURL - Specifies whether to encode the URL or not. If you specify a non-Boolean value, the default value is used. 
Valid values\: true, false 
Default value\: false
    characterSet - The character encoding to be used for the HTTP 'Get' request and response. 
Default value\: UTF-8
    trustAllRoots - Specifies whether to enable weak security over SSL. A SSL certificate is trusted even if no trusted certification authority issued it.
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: true
    keystore - The location of the KeyStore file - a URL or the local path to it. This input is empty if no HTTPS client authentication is used. The default value will be provided if trustAllRoots is false.
Default\: /java/lib/security/cacerts
    keystorePassword - The password associated with the KeyStore file. If trustAllRoots is false and keystore is empty, keystorePassword default will be supplied.
Default value\: changeit
    trustKeystore - The location of the TrustStore file - a URL or the local path to it. This input is empty if no HTTPS server authentication is used. The default value will be provided if trustAllRoots is false.
Default\: /java/lib/security/cacerts
    trustPassword - The password associated with the TrustStore file.  If trustAllRoots is false and trustKeystore is empty, trustPassword default will be supplied.
Default value\: changeit
    kerberosConfFile - The path to the Kerberos configuration file. If this input is empty, the  (Key Distribution Center) and  get their values from the full domain name obtained from the web server URL.
    headerNamesList - A list of header names to be used for the request. 
Example\: Accept,Content-Type
    headerValuesList - A list of header values to be used for the request. 
Example\: text/plain,application/x-www-form-urlencoded
    queryNamesList - A list of query parameter names to be used for the request. 
Example\: parameterName1,parameterName2
    queryValuesList - A list of query parameter values to be used for the request. 
Example\: parameterValue1,parameterValue2
    delimiter - The delimiter used to separate list elements. 
Default value\: (carriage return)

Results\:
    projectId - This is the primary output. The ID of the new project.
    document - The complete document returned by the Http Client POST operation.
    exception - The stack trace of the thrown error (if an error occurred).
    FailureMessage - The final error message returned to the user.

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.
    unknown - The POST was not fully processed, the server responded with an informational response or The specified URL has moved.
